{"info": {"author": "Kazuhiro Suzuki", "author_email": "ksauzzmsg@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: POSIX", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "description": "# Kerberos Ticket Manager\n\n![build status](https://github.com/ksauzz/krbticket/workflows/test/badge.svg)\n\nSimple kinit wrapper to update Kerberos ticket periodically for long running application.\n\n## Getting Started\n\nPeriodical kerberos ticket update\n\n```\nfrom krbticket import KrbTicket\n\nticket = KrbTicket.init(\"<principal>\", \"<keytab path>\")\nticket.updater_start()\n```\n\nIf `keytab path` is not specifyed, kinit uses `KRB5_KTNAME` env, or `/etc/krb5.keytab` to find a keytab file. see: kerberos(1) and kinit(1).\n\n### Ticket Updater Strategies\n\nTo avoid a credential cache (ccache) corruption by concurrent updates from multiple processes, KrbTicketUpdater has a few update strategies:\n\n- SimpleKrbTicketUpdater: for single updater process, or multiple updaters w/ per process ccache. (default)\n- MultiProcessKrbTicketUpdater: for multiple updater processes w/ exclusive file lock\n- SingleProcessKrbTicketUpdater: for multiple updater processes w/ exclusive file lock to restrict the number of updater processes to one against the ccache\n\n```\nfrom krbticket import KrbTicket, SingleProcessKrbTicketUpdater\n\nticket = KrbTicket.init(\"<principal>\", \"<keytab path>\", updater_class=SingleProcessKrbTicketUpdater)\nticket.updater_start()\n```\n\n### Retry\n\nkrbticket supports retry feature utilizing [retrying](https://github.com/rholder/retrying) which provides various retry strategy. To change the behavior, pass the options using `retry_options` of KrbConfig. The dafault values are:\n\n- wait_exponential_multiplier = 1000\n- wait_exponential_multiplier = 30000\n- stop_max_attempt_number = 10\n\n```\nfrom krbticket import KrbTicket\n\nretry_options = {\n  'wait_exponential_multiplier': 1000,\n  'wait_exponential_multiplier': 10000,\n  'stop_max_attempt_number': 5\n}\nticket = KrbTicket.init(\"<principal>\", \"<keytab path>\", retry_options=retry_options)\nticket.updater_start()\n```\n\n### Update Interval\n\nTBD\n\n## Test\n\n```\ndocker run --rm -p 88:88 ksauzz/docker-krb5:0.0.1\npip install -r requirements-test.txt -r requirements.txt\nKRB5_CONFIG=tests/conf/krb5.conf.local pytest\n```\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/ksauzz/krbticket", "keywords": "", "license": "", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "krbticket", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/krbticket/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/krbticket/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/ksauzz/krbticket"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/krbticket/1.0.5/", "requires_dist": ["retrying (==1.3.3)", "fasteners (==0.15)", "pytest ; extra == 'test'", "pytest-cov ; extra == 'test'", "pytest-mock ; extra == 'test'", "flake8 ; extra == 'test'"], "requires_python": "", "summary": "Kerberos Ticket Manager", "version": "1.0.5", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>Kerberos Ticket Manager</h1>\n<p><img alt=\"build status\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/743a31edfe9e8e9c3e4727c25e1578d998aa0dc4/68747470733a2f2f6769746875622e636f6d2f6b7361757a7a2f6b72627469636b65742f776f726b666c6f77732f746573742f62616467652e737667\"></p>\n<p>Simple kinit wrapper to update Kerberos ticket periodically for long running application.</p>\n<h2>Getting Started</h2>\n<p>Periodical kerberos ticket update</p>\n<pre><code>from krbticket import KrbTicket\n\nticket = KrbTicket.init(\"&lt;principal&gt;\", \"&lt;keytab path&gt;\")\nticket.updater_start()\n</code></pre>\n<p>If <code>keytab path</code> is not specifyed, kinit uses <code>KRB5_KTNAME</code> env, or <code>/etc/krb5.keytab</code> to find a keytab file. see: kerberos(1) and kinit(1).</p>\n<h3>Ticket Updater Strategies</h3>\n<p>To avoid a credential cache (ccache) corruption by concurrent updates from multiple processes, KrbTicketUpdater has a few update strategies:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>SimpleKrbTicketUpdater: for single updater process, or multiple updaters w/ per process ccache. (default)</li>\n<li>MultiProcessKrbTicketUpdater: for multiple updater processes w/ exclusive file lock</li>\n<li>SingleProcessKrbTicketUpdater: for multiple updater processes w/ exclusive file lock to restrict the number of updater processes to one against the ccache</li>\n</ul>\n<pre><code>from krbticket import KrbTicket, SingleProcessKrbTicketUpdater\n\nticket = KrbTicket.init(\"&lt;principal&gt;\", \"&lt;keytab path&gt;\", updater_class=SingleProcessKrbTicketUpdater)\nticket.updater_start()\n</code></pre>\n<h3>Retry</h3>\n<p>krbticket supports retry feature utilizing <a href=\"https://github.com/rholder/retrying\" rel=\"nofollow\">retrying</a> which provides various retry strategy. To change the behavior, pass the options using <code>retry_options</code> of KrbConfig. The dafault values are:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>wait_exponential_multiplier = 1000</li>\n<li>wait_exponential_multiplier = 30000</li>\n<li>stop_max_attempt_number = 10</li>\n</ul>\n<pre><code>from krbticket import KrbTicket\n\nretry_options = {\n  'wait_exponential_multiplier': 1000,\n  'wait_exponential_multiplier': 10000,\n  'stop_max_attempt_number': 5\n}\nticket = KrbTicket.init(\"&lt;principal&gt;\", \"&lt;keytab path&gt;\", retry_options=retry_options)\nticket.updater_start()\n</code></pre>\n<h3>Update Interval</h3>\n<p>TBD</p>\n<h2>Test</h2>\n<pre><code>docker run --rm -p 88:88 ksauzz/docker-krb5:0.0.1\npip install -r requirements-test.txt -r requirements.txt\nKRB5_CONFIG=tests/conf/krb5.conf.local pytest\n</code></pre>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 7022737, "releases": {"0.0.1.1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "